history.content:
I really recommend talking to your TA about this.  They can generally point you in the right direction.  Also, I know it can be intimidating, but I also suggest going to talk to Prof HIlfinger in person.  Just ask him how does he suggest you study for the final?   Really.  It can only help your cause if he knows who you are.  Faculty office hours are seldom used and it's really too bad.  

Don't freak out!  You have a lot of time to work on this.  Good luck with it all.  If the stress is getting too much be sure to come by and see us advisors too.

Do all his past exams you can find, check the answers with your friends and make sure you understand every problem. Also, start early on projects, it's not hard to get full credits on projects if you spend enough time on them. 

So don't worry too much for now, start doing the final project ASAP, you still have ~2 weeks, and start reviewing MT1, MT2 material since you didn't do well on them.

Hey everyone, hope Thanksgiving break is going fine.

Im taking 61B rn and unfortunately didn't do well on the midterms. That, plus the fact that my project 1 and 3 score was terribly low means that I need to do really, really well (~36/46) on my final to get the grade I need and declare CS. Already used late drop once, so thats not an option. Anyone who took his class and did well on the final(or if you're in it and doing well rn) - how should I study? What worksheets/topics etc did you find important working on? I feel his lectures aren't very useful, and there's no structure on how to study.

Im freaking out; any and every advice is appreciated. Please please. Thanks.
